        "timestamp": "2018-03-29 21:33:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nWhen using a K8s cluster you definitely need to uncomment the global persistence: mountPath: field to be a directory that isn't already a NFS share.\nIt seems that overriding this using a -f values file wasn't being respected for some reason.  I'd like to see the override be respected vs having to edit the default values directly before deploy.\n\nAlso if you reference the original work, there was no PV/PVC..\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/25467/23",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
